## Preferred Icon Library

Always prefer `@shiu/icons` over `@mui/icons-material` when importing icons.

### Good Example

```typescript
import { EditIcon } from "@shiu/icons";
```

### Bad Example

```typescript
import EditOutlined from "@mui/icons-material/EditOutlined";
```

## Import Multiple Icons in a Single Statement

When importing multiple icons from the same package, combine them into a single import statement.

### Good Example

```typescript
import { DownloadIcon, CopyIcon, BookmarkIcon } from "@shiu/icons";
```

### Bad Example

```typescript
import { DownloadIcon } from "@shiu/icons";
import { CopyIcon } from "@shiu/icons";
import { BookmarkIcon } from "@shiu/icons";
```

## Why?

- `@shiu/icons` provides a consistent, custom icon set for the project
- Ensures visual consistency across the application
- Centralized icon management and customization
- Multiple imports from the same package reduces code readability and increases bundle size

## Icon Sizes

Icons from `@shiu/icons` support the `fontSize` prop to control their size. Available sizes follow Material-UI conventions:

- `small` - 20px (most common for buttons and actions)
- `medium` - 24px (default)
- `large` - 35px
- `inherit` - Inherits font size from parent

### Good Example

```typescript
<DownloadIcon fontSize="small" />
<BookmarkIcon fontSize="medium" />
<EditIcon fontSize="large" />
```

## Usage Examples

### In Icon Buttons

```typescript
import { DownloadIcon, CopyIcon, BookmarkIcon } from "@shiu/icons";
import { MessageActionButton } from "@/features/message-actions/components";

export function MessageActions() {
  return (
    <div>
      <MessageActionButton tooltip="Download message" onClick={onDownload}>
        <DownloadIcon fontSize="small" />
      </MessageActionButton>

      <MessageActionButton tooltip="Copy message" onClick={onCopy}>
        <CopyIcon fontSize="small" />
      </MessageActionButton>

      <MessageActionButton tooltip="Bookmark" onClick={onBookmark}>
        <BookmarkIcon fontSize="small" />
      </MessageActionButton>
    </div>
  );
}
```

### In Buttons

```typescript
import { NewChatIcon } from "@shiu/icons";
import Button from "@mui/material/Button";

export function NewChatButton() {
  return <Button startIcon={<NewChatIcon />}>New Chat</Button>;
}
```

### With Custom Styling

```typescript
import { EditIcon } from "@shiu/icons";

export function CustomIcon() {
  return (
    <EditIcon
      fontSize="small"
      sx={{
        color: "primary.main",
        "&:hover": { opacity: 0.7 },
      }}
    />
  );
}
```
